# Test runner

- **No Jest.** Tests use the hand-rolled harness in
  [`tests/unit/_harness.js`](../../tests/unit/_harness.js). Don't add
  `describe` / `it` / `expect` imports.
- **Default suite must run with no `OPENAI_API_KEY`.** Anything that
  needs the key lives in a separate file (see
  `tests/intent-fixture.js`) and is opt-in.
- **Run locally:** `node tests/unit/run.js`. CI runs the same command.
- New test files end in `.test.js` and live next to other unit tests.
  The runner picks them up by glob; no registration step.
- If a test relies on a fixture, put it in
  `tests/fixtures/audits/<scope>/`. Don't paste large JSON inline.
